localComponents.name: Accordion
localComponents.description: The accordion is used to collapse and expand content to organize it more efficiently. It allows for hiding and displaying content as needed. It reduces clutter and helps maintain the user’s focus by showing only the relevant content at a time.

Key details, such as domain confirmation (e.g., .gov.sa, .edu.sa, .med.sa, .org.sa, .sch.sa), HTTPS usage, and Digital Government Authority registration, reinforce user trust and security.

It typically appears as a small box or pop-up near the element and may contain text, images, or other media to provide context or guidance to the user.
